### CyberShield AI Platform — Demo API Requests
### Works with the VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
### Start the server first: platform serve
### Then click "Send Request" above any request block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

# =============================================================================
# PLATFORM HEALTH
# =============================================================================

### Platform-wide health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

###

# =============================================================================
# 1. URL SHIELD — Phishing Detection
# =============================================================================

### Analyse a suspicious URL (high risk expected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/url/predict
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://paypal-secure-login.xyz/verify?token=abc123"
}

###

### Analyse a legitimate URL (low risk expected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/url/predict
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://github.com/login"
}

###

### Analyse a URL with Claude explanation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/url/explain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://192.168.1.1/admin/phishing-login.php"
}

###

### Batch analyse multiple URLs at once
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/url/predict/batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://google.com",
    "http://secure-paypal-update.tk/login",
    "http://192.168.0.1/bank-verify",
    "https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python",
    "http://amaz0n-account-suspended.xyz/reactivate"
  ]
}

###

### Model info (accuracy, training date, feature count)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/url/model/info

###

# =============================================================================
# 2. CVE INTELLIGENCE — Vulnerability Search
# =============================================================================

### Semantic CVE search — natural language query
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "remote code execution in Apache web servers",
  "k": 5
}

###

### Search with severity filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "SQL injection authentication bypass",
  "k": 5,
  "severity": ["CRITICAL", "HIGH"],
  "start_year": 2021,
  "end_year": 2023
}

###

### Search with CVSS score filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "privilege escalation Windows kernel",
  "k": 8,
  "min_cvss": 8.0,
  "attack_vector": "LOCAL"
}

###

### Ask Claude a question grounded in CVE data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What are the most critical vulnerabilities in Log4j and how can I detect them?",
  "k": 5
}

###

### Look up a specific CVE by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/CVE-2021-44228

###

### CVE index statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cve/stats

###

# =============================================================================
# 3. THREAT INTELLIGENCE — Narratives & Playbooks
# =============================================================================

### Generate a threat narrative for Log4Shell
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/threat/narrative
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cve_id": "CVE-2021-44228"
}

###

### Generate a threat narrative from a free-text description
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/threat/narrative
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "unauthenticated remote code execution in a Java logging library allowing arbitrary LDAP lookups"
}

###

### Generate an incident response playbook for Log4Shell
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/threat/playbook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cve_ids": ["CVE-2021-44228"],
  "organization_context": "mid-size e-commerce company, 5-person SOC, running Java microservices on AWS"
}

###

### Generate a playbook from a description (no CVE ID needed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/threat/playbook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "threat_description": "Ransomware infection detected on Windows file servers, lateral movement observed",
  "organization_context": "healthcare provider, strict HIPAA compliance requirements"
}

###

### Generate a multi-CVE playbook
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/threat/playbook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cve_ids": ["CVE-2021-44228", "CVE-2022-0847", "CVE-2021-4034"],
  "organization_context": "Linux-based infrastructure, Kubernetes cluster"
}

###

# =============================================================================
# 4. ASSET CORRELATION — CVE Matching
# =============================================================================

### Correlate a software inventory against CVE index
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/assets/correlate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assets": [
    { "name": "Apache Log4j", "version": "2.14.1", "asset_type": "library" },
    { "name": "Apache Tomcat", "version": "9.0.54", "asset_type": "web_server" },
    { "name": "OpenSSL", "version": "1.1.1", "asset_type": "library" }
  ],
  "k_per_asset": 5,
  "min_cvss": 7.0,
  "summarize": true
}

###

### Correlate with CISO summary (executive briefing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/assets/correlate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assets": [
    { "name": "Spring Framework", "version": "5.3.0", "asset_type": "framework" },
    { "name": "Jenkins", "version": "2.303", "asset_type": "ci_cd" },
    { "name": "Nginx", "version": "1.18.0", "asset_type": "web_server" },
    { "name": "PostgreSQL", "version": "13.4", "asset_type": "database" }
  ],
  "k_per_asset": 3,
  "min_cvss": 6.0,
  "summarize": true
}

###

# =============================================================================
# 5. RED TEAM — Adversarial URL Generation
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  For authorized penetration testing and phishing simulation ONLY.
# Always provide a valid authorization reference in "authorized_by".

### Generate adversarial variants using all techniques
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/redteam/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "legitimate_domain": "example.com",
  "techniques": ["homoglyphs", "subdomain", "tld_swap", "typos", "encoding", "combo"],
  "count_per_technique": 3,
  "authorized_by": "Demo User / Internal Security Testing"
}

###

### Generate only the highest-risk techniques
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/redteam/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "legitimate_domain": "yourcompany.com",
  "techniques": ["homoglyphs", "subdomain", "combo"],
  "count_per_technique": 4,
  "authorized_by": "Security Team / Phishing Simulation Q1-2025"
}

###
